  "local_port": 39296,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the things you should do for your best friend?",
  "response": "Being a great best friend involves showing up consistently, offering support, and nurturing the relationship. Here are some meaningful things you can do for your best friend:\n\n### **Emotional Support**\n1. **Listen Actively**: Be there to listen without judgment when they need to vent or share their feelings.\n2. **Be Honest**: Offer truthful advice or feedback when asked, but always with kindness.\n3. **Celebrate Their Wins**: Genuinely cheer for their successes, no matter how big or small.\n4. **Be Their Cheerleader**: Encourage them when they\u2019re pursuing their goals or facing challenges.\n5. **Respect Their Boundaries**: Understand and honor their need for space when they need it.\n\n### **Practical Support**\n1. **Help When Needed**: Offer assistance with tasks or errands when they\u2019re overwhelmed.\n2. **Be Dependable**: Follow through on promises and commitments.\n3. **Surprise Them**: Do something thoughtful, like bringing them their favorite snack or small gifts.\n4. **Be Their Safe Space**: Create an environment where they feel comfortable being themselves.\n\n### **Quality Time**\n1. **Spend Time Together**: Make time for shared activities, whether it\u2019s a movie night, a hike, or just hanging out.\n2. **Try New Things**: Suggest fun activities or adventures to keep the friendship exciting.\n3. **Check In Regularly**: Even if you\u2019re busy, a simple text or call can show you care.\n4. **Celebrate Milestones**: Remember important dates like birthdays or anniversaries of their achievements.\n\n### **Understanding and Forgiveness**\n1. **Be Empathetic**: Try to see things from their perspective, especially during disagreements.\n2. **Apologize When Necessary**: Own up to your mistakes and work to make things right.\n3. **Forgive Their Mistakes**: Understand that no one is perfect and give them grace when they slip up.\n4. **Avoid Gossip**: Never talk negatively about them behind their back.\n\n### **Long-Term Commitment**\n1. **Grow Together**: Support each other\u2019s personal growth and evolve as friends over time.\n2. **Accept Changes**: Understand that life circumstances may change, but your bond can remain strong.\n3. **Be Loyal**: Stand by them through thick and thin, and defend them when needed.\n4. **Communicate Openly**: Address issues calmly and honestly to avoid misunderstandings.\n\n### **Celebrate the Friendship**\n1. **Express Gratitude**: Let them know how much you value their friendship.\n2. **Create Memories**: Document your adventures and inside jokes to cherish in the future.\n3. **Be Their Advocate**: Support their dreams and defend their character when others doubt them.\n4. **Be Yourself**: Authenticity strengthens the bond, so don\u2019t be afraid to show your true self.\n\nBeing a best friend is about mutual care, respect, and effort. When you invest in the relationship, it becomes a lifelong source of joy and support.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
